        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 4:54AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 454 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Robbinsville, or near Smoky Mountains-Twentymile
Creek, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smoky Mountains-Fontana Area, Fontana Lake, Fontana Village, Smoky
Mountains-Twentymile Creek, Town Of Santeetlah, Lake Santeetlah,
Smoky Mountains-Kuwohi, Smoky Mountains-Deep Creek, Stecoah, and
Deals Gap.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
